      • addUserIfNotPresent

        @NotNull
@Transactional(isolation=SERIALIZABLE)
public @NotNull UserProfile addUserIfNotPresent​(@NotNull
                                                @NotNull java.lang.String webId)
        Returns the user's profile. If user doesn't exist yet we add them. As SOLID is used for authentication, on the backend side there's a fully transparent way of adding a new user. Returned is a user's profile containing all user's discoveries and executions along with their status (as currently stored in the DB by the ExecutorService)
        Specified by:
        addUserIfNotPresent in interface UserService
        Parameters:
        webId - webId to add / fetch
        Returns:
        user profile

                                     throws UserNotFoundException
        If there's an execution with IRI equal to the provided one on the user profile, it will be removed. Also, if there's only one execution of the pipeline that's being deleted, the pipeline information record is also deleted.

      • deleteDiscovery

        @NotNull
@Transactional(rollbackFor=UserNotFoundException.class)
public @NotNull UserProfile deleteDiscovery​(@NotNull
                                            @NotNull java.lang.String username,
                                            @NotNull
                                            @NotNull java.lang.String discoveryId)
                                     throws UserNotFoundException
        If there's a discovery with ID equal to the provided one on the user profile, it will be removed. Keep in mind that named graphs used with this discovery will be removed as well as there's a DB constraint in place.
        Specified by:
